race.comment: WINNING TOAST (2) was well supported but pulled up with an issue at Warrnambool first-up. He's been freshened and has won a jumpout since. John Allen stays aboard, and he has raced well in stronger than this. Proven second-up and is well placed. THE NARRATOR (1) peaks and has been knocking on the door in better class. Has to carry more weight, but draws inside and he's a live hope. INTIMEOFNEED (12) is also fourth up and ready to win. Raced favourite beaten a whisker at Mornington last time and can sit closer today. She also has winning claims. VADERLEE (11) rates well on his Ballarat effort two back and keep safe with the tongue tie on for the first time. THE MARINER (10) is also going well enough to say he's a hope.
